If using infrared heating, make sure you have enough power for the heating system. Personal saunas are generally heated in two ways: lava rocks, which are heated in a stove and over which water is poured to create steam, or infrared heating, which uses a heater inside the sauna. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Build-Saunas-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-Saunas-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Build-Saunas-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-Saunas-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
